    img(src='image/home_page.jpg' alt='Yuen Tsuen Ancient Trail' width="50%" height="50%")
    p Yuen Chuen Ancient Trail starts from Yuen Long to Tsuen Wan. This trail was major footpath used by villagers before and now is one of the popular trail in North-West New Territories.
    |The trail begins at the staircase opposite Yan On Hospital. After reaching the catchwater, take the steps across the catchwater and climb up to Ha Fa Shan. 
    |Follow the signposts and ascent to Shek Lung Kung. Continue on the paved path to the right and follow the signposts of the Ancient Trail. 
    |After reaching the concrete road, turn left for a short distance. Then take the small path to the right (leaving the Ancient Trail) and head to the campground of Tin Fu Tsai.
    |Join back the Ancient Trail at the main entrance of the campsite. From there, follow the Ancient Trail all the way to Tai Tong, where the trail joins Tai Tong Nature Trail. 
    p 
